                        "designMd":  "---\nname: Titan Industrial\ncolors:\n  surface: \u0027#131313\u0027\n  surface-dim: \u0027#131313\u0027\n  surface-bright: \u0027#393939\u0027\n  surface-container-lowest: \u0027#0e0e0e\u0027\n  surface-container-low: \u0027#1c1b1b\u0027\n  surface-container: \u0027#201f1f\u0027\n  surface-container-high: \u0027#2a2a2a\u0027\n  surface-container-highest: \u0027#353534\u0027\n  on-surface: \u0027#e5e2e1\u0027\n  on-surface-variant: \u0027#c4c7c8\u0027\n  inverse-surface: \u0027#e5e2e1\u0027\n  inverse-on-surface: \u0027#313030\u0027\n  outline: \u0027#8e9192\u0027\n  outline-variant: \u0027#444748\u0027\n  surface-tint: \u0027#c6c6c7\u0027\n  primary: \u0027#ffffff\u0027\n  on-primary: \u0027#2f3131\u0027\n  primary-container: \u0027#e2e2e2\u0027\n  on-primary-container: \u0027#636565\u0027\n  inverse-primary: \u0027#5d5f5f\u0027\n  secondary: \u0027#ffb3b1\u0027\n  on-secondary: \u0027#680011\u0027\n  secondary-container: \u0027#ad0224\u0027\n  on-secondary-container: \u0027#ffb8b5\u0027\n  tertiary: \u0027#ffffff\u0027\n  on-tertiary: \u0027#2f3031\u0027\n  tertiary-container: \u0027#e3e2e2\u0027\n  on-tertiary-container: \u0027#646464\u0027\n  error: \u0027#ffb4ab\u0027\n  on-error: \u0027#690005\u0027\n  error-container: \u0027#93000a\u0027\n  on-error-container: \u0027#ffdad6\u0027\n  primary-fixed: \u0027#e2e2e2\u0027\n  primary-fixed-dim: \u0027#c6c6c7\u0027\n  on-primary-fixed: \u0027#1a1c1c\u0027\n  on-primary-fixed-variant: \u0027#454747\u0027\n  secondary-fixed: \u0027#ffdad8\u0027\n  secondary-fixed-dim: \u0027#ffb3b1\u0027\n  on-secondary-fixed: \u0027#410007\u0027\n  on-secondary-fixed-variant: \u0027#92001c\u0027\n  tertiary-fixed: \u0027#e3e2e2\u0027\n  tertiary-fixed-dim: \u0027#c7c6c6\u0027\n  on-tertiary-fixed: \u0027#1b1c1c\u0027\n  on-tertiary-fixed-variant: \u0027#464747\u0027\n  background: \u0027#131313\u0027\n  on-background: \u0027#e5e2e1\u0027\n  surface-variant: \u0027#353534\u0027\ntypography:\n  display-lg:\n    fontFamily: Anton\n    fontSize: 84px\n    fontWeight: \u0027400\u0027\n    lineHeight: 90px\n    letterSpacing: 0.02em\n  headline-lg:\n    fontFamily: Anton\n    fontSize: 48px\n    fontWeight: \u0027400\u0027\n    lineHeight: 52px\n  headline-lg-mobile:\n    fontFamily: Anton\n    fontSize: 32px\n    fontWeight: \u0027400\u0027\n    lineHeight: 36px\n  title-md:\n    fontFamily: Hanken Grotesk\n    fontSize: 20px\n    fontWeight: \u0027700\u0027\n    lineHeight: 28px\n  body-md:\n    fontFamily: Hanken Grotesk\n    fontSize: 16px\n    fontWeight: \u0027400\u0027\n    lineHeight: 24px\n  label-sm:\n    fontFamily: JetBrains Mono\n    fontSize: 12px\n    fontWeight: \u0027500\u0027\n    lineHeight: 16px\n    letterSpacing: 0.05em\nspacing:\n  unit: 8px\n  gutter: 24px\n  margin-desktop: 64px\n  margin-mobile: 20px\n  container-max: 1440px\n---\n\n## Brand \u0026 Style\n\nThis design system is forged in the aesthetic of heavy-duty performance and industrial grit. It is engineered for a target audience that values strength, durability, and a no-nonsense approach to athletic excellence. The visual language is unapologetically bold, drawing heavily from **High-Contrast / Bold** and **Brutalist** influences to evoke a sense of \"Iron Tough\" reliability.\n\nThe emotional response should be one of motivation and uncompromising power. Large-scale typography acts as a structural element, while a moody, monochromatic base is punctuated by high-visibility accents. The interface should feel like high-end gym equipment: heavy, precise, and built to last.\n\nKey stylistic pillars:\n- **Raw Texture:** Use of grit, concrete-like overlays, and high-grain photography.\n- **Architectural Hierarchy:** Massive headlines that dominate the screen real estate.\n- **Functional Density:** Information is presented clearly with a focus on technical specifications and performance metrics.\n\n## Colors\n\nThe palette is rooted in a \"Deep Forge\" dark mode. It utilizes a high-contrast relationship between deep charcoal foundations and stark white primary elements to ensure maximum legibility under intense conditions.\n\n- **Primary (White):** Used for headlines and primary actions to cut through the dark atmosphere.\n- **Secondary (Crimson Pulse):** Reserved for urgent calls to action, \"on sale\" indicators, and critical performance alerts.\n- **Tertiary (Steel Gray):** Used for borders, secondary text, and inactive states.\n- **Neutral (Obsidian):** The foundation of the UI, using varying shades of near-black to create depth without losing the moody aesthetic.\n\nAvoid soft gradients; use solid blocks of color or hard-edged transitions to maintain the industrial feel.\n\n## Typography\n\nTypography is the most critical asset in this design system. We utilize **Anton** for headlines to provide a towering, condensed presence that mimics industrial signage. **Hanken Grotesk** provides a modern, legible balance for body copy, while **JetBrains Mono** is used for technical labels and \"specs\" to reinforce the engineering aspect of the brand.\n\n**Hierarchy Rules:**\n- All headlines must be uppercase.\n- Display type should use tight tracking to emphasize density.\n- Labels and secondary meta-data should use monospaced fonts to look like serial numbers or technical stamps.\n\n## Layout \u0026 Spacing\n\nThe layout follows a **Fixed Grid** system for desktop to maintain a premium, editorial feel, switching to a fluid model for mobile. We use an 8px spacing rhythm to ensure mathematical precision across all components.\n\n- **Desktop:** 12-column grid with generous 64px outer margins to allow the content to \"breathe\" despite the heavy visual style.\n- **Mobile:** 4-column grid with 20px margins.\n- **Vertical Rhythm:** Large sections should be separated by significant white space (80px+) to prevent the high-contrast elements from becoming overwhelming.\n\nContent should often be center-aligned in featured sections to create a \"heroic\" focus, while product grids should remain strictly aligned to the left for scanability.\n\n## Elevation \u0026 Depth\n\nThis system rejects soft shadows and traditional depth. Instead, it uses **Tonal Layers** and **Bold Outlines** to define hierarchy.\n\n- **Stacking:** Surface levels are defined by slight shifts in neutral hex codes (e.g., shifting from #121212 to #1A1A1A).\n- **Borders:** Use 1px or 2px solid strokes in Steel Gray or White to define card boundaries and input fields.\n- **Backdrop:** Backgrounds should utilize high-grain image overlays or subtle \"noise\" textures to simulate raw materials like steel or asphalt.\n- **Focus:** Elements \"pop\" not through elevation, but through stark color inversion (e.g., a white button on a black background).\n\n## Shapes\n\nThe shape language is strictly **Sharp (0)**. There are no rounded corners in this design system. Every button, card, and input field features hard 90-degree angles. This reinforces the industrial, \"built\" nature of the gear and aligns with the condensed, blocky nature of the typography.\n\nInternal elements like icons should also follow a sharp-angled or heavy-stroke geometric style.\n\n## Components\n\n### Buttons\n- **Primary:** Solid white background, black Anton text, uppercase. No border. Hard corners.\n- **Secondary:** Ghost style. 2px white border, white text, no background.\n- **Hover States:** Immediate color inversion. No soft transitions.\n\n### Cards\n- **Product Cards:** Full bleed imagery at the top. Hard black background for the info area. White text for titles, gray for prices.\n- **Badges:** Use the Secondary (Crimson Pulse) color for \"NEW\" or \"SALE\" badges, placed in the top-right corner with 0px radius.\n\n### Input Fields\n- Solid black background with a 1px Steel Gray border. \n- Text turns white on focus with the border becoming white.\n- Labels use JetBrains Mono in uppercase above the field.\n\n### Progress Bars / Performance Metrics\n- Heavy, thick bars using the Secondary color to show completion or intensity.\n- Always include a monospaced percentage or value label for a \"technical readout\" look.\n\n### Icons\n- Thick stroke (2px min), geometric, and strictly monochromatic. Avoid any rounded terminals on icon paths.",
